<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-31T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-31T17:00:00-05:00" n="668" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d668">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">484.11 Young, Reuben S., No. 2/17:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Southard</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-31T18:00:00-04:00">August 31, 1934—6
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>15. Your 11, August 25, 4 p.m. Although an offer of two thousand
                                Ethiopian dollars in full settlement of Young’s claim appears to be
                                    <pb facs="0880" n="780" xml:id="pg_780"/> somewhat
                                incommensurate with the gravity of the offense, you may inform the
                                competent Ethiopian authorities that this Government is prepared to
                                accept the offer provided that payment is made without delay. You
                                may also state that this Government notes with satisfaction that the
                                Ethiopian official responsible for the treaty violation is to be
                                punished.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>